HEADWORD: Altrices
<hw>Al*tri"ces</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.,
nourishes, pl. of <ets>altrix</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Nursers, -- a term applied to those birds whose young are hatched
in a very immature and helpless condition, so as to require the care of
their parents for some time; -- opposed to
<contr>pr⟦ae⟧coces</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>altricial</ent>⟦br⟧
